- "vast oceans" metaphorically refers to countries;
- "waves of competitive sports" metaphorically refers to leagues;
- More than a hundred waves means more than 100 leagues;
- "hosting" refers to countries that have these leagues.

The term "impactful factors" refers to the combination of win rate values and weight values; the higher the product, the more impactful the factor is considered. The "top three" implies that only the three most impactful factors per league are of interest.;
Win rates may refer to historical performance statistics indicating the likelihood of a team’s success in that league.;
Weight types could include various performance metrics such as goal difference, team form, or team name, each with its own value.
